messages.message: Would anyone know why `test_user/tests/fs/Instabase Drive` was at some point moved to `test_user/tests/fs/Old drive`  on dogfood/uat? Some classifier cypress tests are breaking as a result
Maybe part of the dogfood/prod split? It’s possible the prod “Instabase Drive” drive got mounted as “Old Drive”
Not sure how recently you’ve noticed the regression
Just noticed it recently, but haven't been monitoring the cypress test much. I'd be surprised if this was a holdover from the dogfood/prod split though, this was working in previous UATs
